                    "body": "bq. For that from_pandas call, the error is expected I think, although we currently don't have an option to allow this (to indicate you are OK with losing data).\u00a0\r\n\r\nActually, I am mistaken here, and we already have a {{safe}} option here:\r\n\r\n{code:python}\r\n>>> table = pa.Table.from_pandas(df, schema=pyarrow_schema, safe=False) \r\n>>> table                                                                                                                                                                                                     \r\npyarrow.Table\r\ndatetime_ms: timestamp[ms]\r\nmetadata\r\n--------\r\n{b'pandas': ...\r\n\r\n>>> table.to_pandas()  \r\n              datetime_ms\r\n0 2019-06-21 22:13:02.901\r\n{code}",
